The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | CAB to demand reimbursement
                                                                                                                                                                                                     CAB to demand reimbursement
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) will send a letter on Wednesday to Red Chillies Entertainment Private Ltd, the franchise owner of the Kolkata Knight Riders, and the Indian Premier League (IPL) governing body, seeking reimbursement of the funds spent by the association while hosting the matches.         
	The move was decided on Monday by the CABs IPL committee, headed by Srinjoy Bose, after having a close look at the audit report of the expenses incurred during the inaugural tournament.         
	We will send a letter to the Red Chillies authorities and a copy of it to the IPL governing body, Bose said after the meeting. The association had spent Rs 7.26 crore to host the seven matches and now we want the franchise owner to repay the amount. We have spent it to make it a success So we expect them to repay us the amount, Bose added.         
	It was also learnt that the CAB will decide on their course of action only after getting a reply.                                                                                                                          
